--- !u!114 &885219562
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 885219558}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: fce8b1ddf3655624590e578fb42cb521, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CompanyInteraction
  questionMark: {fileID: 1252062850}
  companyPanel: {fileID: 2057730542}
  resultPanel: {fileID: 2057730542}
  companyTitleText: {fileID: 1603052537}
  companyBodyText: {fileID: 899156377}
  hintText: {fileID: 877619149}
  resultTitleText: {fileID: 1603052537}
  resultBodyText: {fileID: 899156377}
  resultButtonText: {fileID: 0}
  companyName: <color=#6B4712><size=125%><b>Mid Tier Company</b></size></color>
  requirementText: '<color=#6B4712><b>Job Description:</b></color>

    Entry-level
    role. Responsibilities include printing documents, making coffee, fixing random
    spreadsheet issues, and occasionally doing the job you actually applied for.


    <color=#6B4712><b>Qualification:</b></color>

    Resume
    score 65+.

    Networking mini-game required.

    Must look "professional"
    while doing low-impact tasks.


    <color=#6B4712><b>Offer:</b></color>

    Minimum
    wage.

    Negotiable, but somehow only downward.'
  companyTier: mid_tier
  successResultBody: "<color=#2E7D32><b>APPLICATION RESULT: ACCEPTED</b></color>\nCongratulations.
    Your application has been approved by the hiring committee.\nAfter reviewing
    many candidates, they determined that your resume is\n\u201Cacceptable enough
    to continue the process.\u201D\n\nYour responsibilities will include:\n\u2022
    Printing documents no one reads  \n\u2022 Fixing spreadsheets created in 2009 
    \n\u2022 Attending meetings that could have been emails  \n\nOccasionally, you
    may also perform the job you actually applied for. Please report on Monday with
    a professional attitude and low expectations."
  requirementBlockedResultBody: "<color=#B36B00><b>APPLICATION RESULT: REQUIREMENTS
    NOT MET</b></color>\nYour application cannot proceed at this time.\n\n<color=#6B4712><b>Required
    Minimum:</b></color>\nTo apply for this position you must have\n\u2022 Resume
    score: 65+  \n\u2022 At least one real project that actually works  \n\u2022
    Must already survive one Startup company first.\n\nCurrent status: requirements
    not satisfied.\n\nPlease complete the missing items and return when your resume
    looks\nslightly more \u201Ccorporate approved.\u201D"
  declinedResultBody: "<color=#8B0000><b>APPLICATION RESULT: DECLINED</b></color>\nYour
    application was reviewed by HR.\n\nThis is difficult to say, but please do not
    feel depressed. Your resume already looks depressed enough on its own.\n\nAccording
    to company policy, we will keep your resume on file for the next 6 months in
    case a suitable position appears.\n\nPlease rest assured: it will most likely
    never be looked at again. Realistically, it will sit quietly in a folder called
    \"Future Opportunities\" along with several thousand other resumes.\t\t"
